e transition into primetime television, working on popular shows such as The Avengers, Space: 1999 and The Adventures of Black Beauty. Featuring first-hand testimony from colleagues ranging from Dame Judi Dench and Petula Clark to John Cleese and Sir Michael Palin, this riveting account of Crichton’s fascinating life in film will appeal to film scholars and general readers alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszGreat Britain. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2021. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aA Fish Called Wanda.  aAlexander Korda.  aCult television.  aDenham Studios.  aEaling Studios.  aEaling comedies.  aFilm editing.  aHollywood.  aMichael Balcon.  aThe Avengers.1 aFalk, Quentin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614996140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526149961423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526149961/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles